original:
Cells are the fundamental units of life, typically ranging in size from 1 to 100 micrometers, making them visible only under light or electron microscopes. There are two primary types of cells: eukaryotic and prokaryotic. 

Eukaryotic cells possess a nucleus and can be either unicellular or multicellular organisms. In contrast, prokaryotic cells lack a nucleus and are primarily represented by single-celled organisms such as bacteria. In
